# Deploy and document after every change

When you finish modifying this project:

## 1. Update docs when features change

If you add, remove, or materially change user-facing behavior, update:

- **`README.md`** — Features, Usage table, Project layout
- **`manifest.json`** — `description` (shown in Blish module settings)

Keep manifest description concise (1–2 sentences). README can be more detailed.

## 2. Build and deploy

```powershell
$env:GW2_BLISH_EXE = "C:\Path\To\Blish HUD.exe"   # optional
.\deploy.ps1
```

Do not skip deploy unless the build failed and could not be fixed.

**Target:** `%USERPROFILE%\Documents\Guild Wars 2\addons\blishhud\modules\` (or OneDrive Documents if synced)

**Blish exe:** set `GW2_BLISH_EXE` to auto-restart after deploy

## 3. Releases

For Blish Module Repo publishing: see local `PUBLISH.md` and `SSRD_PROFILE.md` (gitignored).

## Encoding

If build reports `\0` / UTF-16 errors on `.cs` files, see `.cursor/rules/blish-csharp.mdc`.
